# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Project: Crystalsweep
# File: .env.example
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Purpose:
# This file provides an example configuration for CrystalSweep. Copy this file to
# .env and modify the values to match your beamline setup.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# ==============================================================================
# AREA DETECTOR CONFIGURATION
# ==============================================================================

# PV name for the Area Detector image stream (EPICS PVA NTNDArray)
# This should point to the PVA plugin image PV on your Area Detector IOC
#
# Examples:
#   - Eiger detector:  13EIG1:Pva1:Image
#   - Pilatus detector: 13PIL1:Pva1:Image
#   - Simulation IOC:   13SIM1:Pva1:Image
#
# To find the correct PV name for your detector:
# 1. Check your Area Detector IOC startup scripts
# 2. Look for NDPluginPva plugin configuration
# 3. The PV name is typically: <PREFIX><PLUGIN>:Image
#    where PREFIX is your detector prefix (e.g., "13EIG1:")
#    and PLUGIN is the PVA plugin name (e.g., "Pva1")
#
# Default: 13SIM1:Pva1:Image (simulation detector)
AD_VIEWER_PV=13SIM1:Pva1:Image

# ==============================================================================
# NOTES
# ==============================================================================
#
# Setting up Area Detector for PVA streaming:
# -------------------------------------------
# Your Area Detector IOC must have the NDPluginPva (PVA plugin) configured.
# In your IOC's st.cmd or similar, you should have lines like:
#
#   NDPvaConfigure("PVA1", $(QSIZE), 0, "$(PORT)", 0, $(PREFIX)Pva1:, 0, 0, 0)
#   dbLoadRecords("NDPva.template", "P=$(PREFIX),R=Pva1:,PORT=PVA1,...")
#   startPVAServer
#
# Verifying the PV is available:
# ------------------------------
# You can test if the PV is accessible using:
#   pvget <PV_NAME>
# Or use pvlist to see all available PVs:
#   pvlist
#
# Testing with areaDetector simDetector:
# --------------------------------------
# The easiest way to test is using the EPICS areaDetector simDetector IOC:
# 1. Start the simDetector IOC (typically in areaDetector/ADSimDetector/iocs/simDetectorIOC/iocBoot/iocSimDetector/)
# 2. Make sure the PVA plugin is enabled
# 3. Set AD_VIEWER_PV to match your simDetector prefix (default often 13SIM1:)
#
